export {};
// Access Modifiers control the visibility and accessibility of class members, such as properties and methods aligning with the principles of encapsulation and information hiding in object-oriented programming.
// Public: Members are accessible from anywhere; this is the default modifier if none is specified.
// Private: Members are accessible only within the class they are defined in.
// Protected: Members are accessible within the class they are defined in and in subclasses.
//              |  Parent Class    Child Class    Outer Class   |
// Public       |       ✅             ✅             ✅       |
// Protected    |       ✅             ✅             ❌       |
// Private      |       ✅             ❌             ❌       |
